&lt;h2 id="chapter-5-working-with-text-files">Chapter 5: Working with Text Files
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Most Linux configuration is done by editing plain text files. Whether you&amp;rsquo;re modifying files in the &lt;code>/etc&lt;/code> directory to configure local services or editing Ansible playbooks to manage hosts, plain text files are everywhere in these tasks.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>